The paper deals with robotic manipulation, which falls under the category of robotics and automation (cs.RO). The task of folding a garment involves visual perception and understanding of deformable objects, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as likely sub-categories. The use of optimization techniques to find an optimal trajectory also suggests machine learning (cs.LG) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of simulation to predict the behavior of the garment suggests systems and control (cs.SY) as another possible sub-category.
